wikipedia_page.main: Sir Norman Lane Jude (7 April 1905 – 18 February 1975) was a politician in South Australia.

response: Cameron entered South Australia's Legislative Council in 1971 following the retirement of Sir Norman Jude. He became an important ally of Steele Hall (now Leader of the Opposition), representing the increasingly visible moderate forces within the party. Cameron often opposed his fellow LCL Legislative Councillors, due to his support for Universal Suffrage for that chamber.
